data.content:
Now I have all the details. Here are the **4 breaking changes** and their fixes:

---

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` types removed (`OpenApiString`)

`IOpenApiAny`, `OpenApiString`, etc. are gone in OpenAPI.NET v2. `Schema.Example` is now `JsonNode?`.

```diff
- using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
+ using System.Text.Json.Nodes;

- param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");
+ param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

### 2. `Schema.Nullable` removed

OpenAPI 3.1 represents nullability via the `Type` flags enum (`JsonSchemaType`). There is no `Nullable` property.

```diff
- property.Value.Nullable = false;
+ property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

To **set** nullable: `property.Value.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;`

---

### 3. `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` removed — use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`

References are now separate types. `OpenApiSecurityScheme` no longer has a `Reference` property.

```diff
- var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
- {
-     Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
- };
+ var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

---

### 4. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` dictionary key changed

It now inherits `Dictionary<OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference, List<string>>` (was `Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>`). The value type also changed to `List<string>`.

```diff
  operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
  {
-     new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
+     new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }
  };
```

(Where `scopes` must be `List<string>`, not `IList<string>` or `string[]`.)

---

### Full fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0` upgraded its dependency from **Microsoft.OpenApi 1.x** to **2.x**, which adds OpenAPI 3.1 support and restructures the object model accordingly.
